Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.30,0:34:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,got about as far as 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.57,0:34:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.07,0:34:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to contrast that with a level of awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.84,0:34:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which has to do with the 600 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.88,0:34:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.98,0:34:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And classically, the great teacher in certain is called an Arhat,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.86,0:34:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and Arhat is at 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.76,0:34:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the witness observer at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.92,0:34:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the witness observer is a very reachable level
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.07,0:34:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you constantly surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.17,0:35:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're constantly surrendering the desire to experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.80,0:35:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So let go your addiction to experiencing experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.13,0:35:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the short and fastest way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.21,0:35:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The fastest way to enlightenment is to surrender your desire
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.90,0:35:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and craving to experience experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.80,0:35:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you allow that you disappear it as it begins to rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.48,0:35:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel the energy of interest beginning to attach to a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.38,0:35:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.01,0:35:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You nip it in the bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.78,0:35:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll reach a point where you're no longer experiencing experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.71,0:35:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is just the hip list from which you can do anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.17,0:35:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,including leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.53,0:35:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing into one's self nature is a Buddhist term
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.23,0:35:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Buddha did not like to use the term God
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.80,0:35:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because he thought it was so misleading.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.13,0:35:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has their own opinions about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.73,0:35:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you use the term God,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.05,0:36:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to be looking for a projection of their own definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.07,0:36:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is the ultimate is not definable,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.21,0:36:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly not within linear conceptual terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.40,0:36:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha thought it wiser to give it no name
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.11,0:36:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and just if you let go of your attachments,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.73,0:36:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of your attachments and aversions to the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.57,0:36:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,stop identifying with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.21,0:36:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you will come into the presence of the infinite non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.94,0:36:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.09,0:36:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing into one's self nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.07,0:36:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,On the way there, you may go through the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.46,0:36:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And people are afraid of the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.78,0:36:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them, don't be afraid of the void
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.19,0:36:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.76,0:36:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing good about the boogeyman,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.69,0:36:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there ain't no boogeyman in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.07,0:36:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't no boogeyman there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.61,0:36:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll become nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.42,0:36:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's your problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.71,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be something, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.03,0:37:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego wants to be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.32,0:37:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the ego is afraid of becoming nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.90,0:37:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.09,0:37:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be nobody and a nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.98,0:37:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you want to be a nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.57,0:37:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with being nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.23,0:37:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't have any problems at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.76,0:37:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No taxes, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.96,0:37:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody will be looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.30,0:37:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You go through the void of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.53,0:37:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you stop experiencing experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.19,0:37:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,everything becomes still and infinite and self-evident.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.69,0:37:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.46,0:37:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.61,0:37:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.65,0:37:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.73,0:37:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is complete and total and self-evident.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.36,0:37:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.63,0:37:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.55,0:37:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.17,0:37:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.71,0:37:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to transcend the void?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.42,0:37:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already covered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.57,0:37:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The void of seeming nothingness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.30,0:37:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that's only a seeming nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.05,0:38:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because beyond the nothingness is infinite love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.96,0:38:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you then also refuse the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.13,0:38:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.71,0:38:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse the void, having been there before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.86,0:38:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But now with a different awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.75,0:38:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That divinity was infinite love and it was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.26,0:38:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So this time there was the refusal of the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.07,0:38:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,negated as this is not the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.15,0:38:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate reality is radiant with an infinite, exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.30,0:38:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,gentle, infinitely powerful love that is its essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.86,0:38:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you know you're there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.26,0:38:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point everything turns stunningly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.01,0:38:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the radiance of all, all shines forth with the radiance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.17,0:38:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity as its essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.05,0:38:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of all existence is divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.44,0:39:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So oneness, we're talking in 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.09,0:39:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is consciousness, which is the realm of our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.44,0:39:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.84,0:39:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see consciousness itself still lacks awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.48,0:39:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.80,0:39:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there is the awareness of what's going on in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.65,0:39:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the attributes of God, omniscience, omnipresence, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.13,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just qualities of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.36,0:39:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not what God is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.13,0:39:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are qualities which is an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.57,0:39:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we look at these things, this is what we call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.65,0:39:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the automatic consequence of the reality of divinity itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.15,0:39:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.92,0:39:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now we get to the great avatars, the Buddha at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.11,0:39:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ at 1,000, Krishna at 1,000, and then we get to divinity itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.01,0:40:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,God as creator, God as divinity, and now we're dealing with they calibrate at infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.90,0:40:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.09,0:40:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the paradigm of science is linear, provable, it's in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.13,0:40:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality is extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.17,0:40:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality is experiential and radically subjective, radically subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.84,0:40:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, science is paranoid about the radically subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.92,0:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and really doesn't know whether the first person is a valid contributor to data.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.50,0:40:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The first person is subjective, what people say, I, the experience of the I.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.65,0:40:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So science could not possibly validate spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.96,0:40:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because all spiritual reality is the witnessing of the personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.73,0:41:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So conferences on consciousness and that exclude the first person narrative
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.51,0:41:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all calibrate about 410 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.09,0:41:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They're supposed to be on science and spirituality or science and religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.13,0:41:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't possibly be at 410, calibration level 410.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.05,0:41:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.46,0:41:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because experiential is 500 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.50,0:41:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on then to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.17,0:41:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.26,0:41:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think these will come out okay once we get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.25,0:41:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.01,0:41:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just the terms used for level 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.23,0:41:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's what the experience is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.46,0:41:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite peacefulness, inner silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.07,0:41:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is still, everything is exquisite, and that's why it's bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.86,0:41:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.98,0:41:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's sat chetananda, it's total and it's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.42,0:41:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's non-local, non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.78,0:41:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.94,0:42:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.09,0:42:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.21,0:42:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that how we decided to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.38,0:42:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we did, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.78,0:42:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I said must be sold at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.76,0:42:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad it ain't still true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.09,0:42:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.17,0:42:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This self-realization then, the pathway that we, the pathway to God through truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.34,0:42:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.17,0:42:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The only science of religion I know of is the one we teach, actually, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.03,0:42:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, consciousness research is a clinical science, not academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.30,0:42:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinical science at least gives us some dimension of where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.17,0:42:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-realization then results in compassion, timelessness, essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.17,0:42:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Self is God-imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.09,0:42:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And one, it is a gift of grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.63,0:43:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace is hard to obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.55,0:43:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.21,0:43:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace means, from a logical viewpoint, not earned, not sought for, not accomplished,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.26,0:43:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but a given.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.55,0:43:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at level 600, one experiences very vividly that the condition is one of grace, one of grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.40,0:43:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace is also a frequency within the aura, and those who have been in a state of grace
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.32,0:43:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now have within their aura the energy, the frequency, and the vibration of that grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.30,0:43:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's called the grace of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.73,0:43:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.34,0:43:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see creation as an unfoldment, unfoldment, and emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.07,0:43:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.46,0:44:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We repeat that over and over in all lectures, because it's such a roadblock.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.40,0:44:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.61,0:44:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.61,0:44:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,everything has a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.86,0:44:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And under appropriate conditions, that potential becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.78,0:44:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what you're seeing is the emergence of potentiality when the conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.73,0:44:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one of the conditions that makes things appropriate, and that facilitates their emergence,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.38,0:44:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is spiritual energy itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.36,0:44:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, many things sit idle, and the minute, not the minute, but under the influence of spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.38,0:44:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy, things begin to manifest that would not manifest otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.73,0:44:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it tends to precipitate what the world calls the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.73,0:44:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When the world notices this, then the world calls that miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.25,0:44:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To the people of advanced consciousness, it's not miraculous at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.40,0:45:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way things come about naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.84,0:45:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.78,0:45:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When the weather is warm and the wind is right, the bird takes off.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.19,0:45:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.90,0:45:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But he can't take off unless the wind direction is in such a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.38,0:45:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, intention, the power of intention then, which brings us to the Heisenberg Principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.07,0:45:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the only real crossover to me in science and spiritual reality is the Heisenberg Principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.09,0:45:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery that intention collapses the wave function from the potential to the actual,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.57,0:45:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so that that which could be now manifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.13,0:45:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as is, it brings into is-ness that which could be under appropriate conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.42,0:45:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, no research has been done on measuring the power of the consciousness level of the observer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.01,0:45:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and its effect on the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.98,0:46:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we know from history that the higher the level of the consciousness of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.17,0:46:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the likelihood of the miraculous to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.50,0:46:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, creation then is an eternal, endless evolutionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.26,0:46:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,very unfolding, and it seems mystical and unlikely because it's beyond cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.21,0:46:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these states then of witnessing can be reached relatively easily by contemplation and meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.88,0:46:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One can become, without any effort really, the observer witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.36,0:46:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be the observer witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.32,0:46:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you decline making any comments about what you witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.92,0:46:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All comments, nobody cares your opinion about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.71,0:46:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give it a name, you don't have to figure it out, you don't have to label it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.71,0:46:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You just witness it without doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.46,0:46:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a great discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.67,0:47:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind wants to do something with it, wants to make it pretty, wants to make it right, wants to make it wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.55,0:47:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to get it, wants to get even with it, wants to conquer it, wants to mate with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.98,0:47:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat it, put it in your bank account, vote for it, you know, do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.34,0:47:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.01,0:47:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just sit there, blogger. Do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.98,0:47:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a protest march, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.59,0:47:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm protesting. I have a protest march against bloggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.84,0:47:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a blog-a-phobe.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.59,0:47:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A blog-a-phobe.
