Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.44,1:00:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty well displayed in the quotes in the articles. It says, you know, scientists are outraged and indignant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.42,1:00:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a scientist who's outraged and indignant, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.80,1:00:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's ism, scientism. When it's a scientism, then science gets outraged and indignant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.17,1:00:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Outraged and indignant. It gets all huffed up about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.42,1:00:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they end up writing a book like...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.67,1:00:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Dawkins. He missed it by one letter. Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.23,1:01:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we have a real paradox. He writes a book called The God Delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.03,1:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary State 190. Extremely arrogant. Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.76,1:01:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is a man who writes a book about delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.25,1:01:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And this man here has a delusion that God is a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.21,1:01:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks God is a delusion. He writes a book called The God Delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.44,1:01:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's his delusion. So he wants to share his delusion with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.88,1:01:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing your delusion, Mr. Dawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.00,1:01:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That just struck me as so funny when I saw that I was a God delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.09,1:01:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a delusion that God's a delusion. It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.76,1:02:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because in the domain of his reality, it is a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.01,1:02:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no proof possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.90,1:02:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you live in a world where nothing is real unless it's provable, demonstrable, and verifiable,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.21,1:02:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't measure it or weigh it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.07,1:02:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then from his paradigm of reality, God would then be a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.46,1:02:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That is certainly understandable as a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.44,1:02:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if that was your only way of...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.92,1:02:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If your only capability was pedestrian logic,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.51,1:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then you would be pretty much stuck with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.86,1:02:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-religionism and scientism tend to be about the same ilk.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.23,1:02:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are all about 180 or 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So whenever you see secular this, secular that,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.01,1:02:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know right away they're going to be below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.07,1:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanistic reductionism, natural skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.65,1:02:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is sort of being brought up in a slightly negative way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.50,1:03:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a child brought up surrounded by love and affirmation,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.92,1:03:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be trusting rather than skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.92,1:03:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My downside is naivete.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.36,1:03:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can sell me the Brooklyn Bridge, that's been my...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.36,1:03:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've needed guardians to keep me from buying the Brooklyn Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.36,1:03:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to donate it, and then you find there's taxes due,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.78,1:03:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why they want to donate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.78,1:03:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.78,1:03:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So scientism then becomes a religion in itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.78,1:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you really...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.00,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not science versus religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.00,1:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's two religions banging against each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.00,1:03:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because scientism is just another religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.00,1:03:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.00,1:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you put your faith in it as the ultimate truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.00,1:03:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you put your faith in as the ultimate truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.00,1:03:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that is your religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.00,1:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just religionized it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.00,1:03:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is no facts except the provable facts of science,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.51,1:04:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're now a religionist, a religionist.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.51,1:04:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Natural skepticism, as I said, to me is somebody who was brought up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.98,1:04:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to be slightly untrusting, untrusting.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.36,1:04:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The world I lived in was so worthy of trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.36,1:04:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, everybody went to church.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.36,1:04:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was moral.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.36,1:04:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cheated anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.36,1:04:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was up front.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.94,1:04:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your neighbor returned your grass mower when he was done with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.13,1:04:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't steal it or sell it on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.63,1:04:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no reason to distrust anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.63,1:04:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I never thought of distrusting anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.63,1:04:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a novel idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.76,1:04:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people, like the local bullies,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.03,1:04:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't that you mistrusted them.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.73,1:04:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you knew them too well.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.73,1:04:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't that I mistrusted he was going to be a bully.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.73,1:04:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he was waiting for me around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.73,1:05:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I took boxing lessons.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.92,1:05:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And learned how to give him a bloody nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.30,1:05:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the end of that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.55,1:05:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's sweat.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.75,1:05:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's what the article called natural skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.75,1:05:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which is sort of a negative way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.75,1:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanistic reductionism is the most pedestrian way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.57,1:05:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the basis of all these skeptics.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.63,1:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the so-called bottom-up view of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.63,1:05:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our view is from top down.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.76,1:05:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've confirmed over and over again that all of creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.76,1:05:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at infinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.76,1:05:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the consequence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.76,1:05:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom-up thinks that we all are descendants of monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.98,1:05:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they call it the Scopes Monkey Trial.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.98,1:06:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That what has come to be has done so as a result of accidental evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.23,1:06:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Accidental.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.23,1:06:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.23,1:06:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they don't like that term either.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.23,1:06:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.71,1:06:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But things just went bumpity bump in the night millions and billions of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.71,1:06:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally certain things worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.71,1:06:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And they worked out accidentally.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.96,1:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm writing about it right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.96,1:06:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm sort of up on the topic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.96,1:06:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you don't see intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.96,1:06:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you watch the Blue Planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.96,1:06:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows on Channel 8 once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.03,1:06:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Blue Planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.03,1:06:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all about the life at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.03,1:06:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredibly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.03,1:06:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredibly beautiful photography.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.03,1:06:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see these incredibly magnificent creatures.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.03,1:06:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only incredibly beautiful, magical, mysterious and wondrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.03,1:06:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But from a scientific viewpoint, they're mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.21,1:06:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They can detect electrical waves from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.32,1:07:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then light up little things that look like food to somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.34,1:07:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's actually, gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.34,1:07:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the emergence of intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.57,1:07:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.57,1:07:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the intelligence of the design of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.40,1:07:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at all of life, especially in great nature movies,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.88,1:07:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the quickest way to see it is something like the Blue Planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.88,1:07:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You become aware of the intrinsic emergence of intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.07,1:07:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredible intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.42,1:07:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How you can make electricity at the bottom of the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.42,1:07:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,under that kind of pressure, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.42,1:07:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to me, intelligence is also evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.42,1:07:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.59,1:07:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's innate to the gift of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.00,1:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.00,1:07:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we took care of that Dawkins fella.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.28,1:07:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll beat him up till he gets rid of his delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.34,1:08:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.34,1:08:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Dawkins, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.88,1:08:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we send him our love and goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.40,1:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.78,1:08:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as he apologizes, we'll apologize too.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.77,1:08:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.77,1:08:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our God is a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.77,1:08:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an enemy of ours.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.77,1:08:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we'd better kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.77,1:08:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think so?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.77,1:08:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.77,1:08:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, you can't become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.77,1:08:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.90,1:08:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You never make it through the tight corners.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.90,1:08:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.90,1:08:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.10,1:08:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humor is coming from a greater context.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.10,1:08:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,From a greater context, you see that which is...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.19,1:08:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is stingy and cramped and small.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.19,1:08:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.19,1:08:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to do it with humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.19,1:08:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.19,1:08:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.19,1:09:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to finish up the new slides this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.39,1:09:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.39,1:09:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.77,1:09:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We only got...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.77,1:09:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still on number 100.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.77,1:09:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you weren't quite done with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.77,1:09:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.77,1:09:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're done.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.77,1:09:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to finish them by lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.81,1:09:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.81,1:09:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.81,1:09:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We stop at 1230.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.64,1:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's about 45 minutes from now.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.50,1:09:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.50,1:09:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.50,1:09:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll finish it up then.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.50,1:09:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.50,1:09:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions thus far?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.84,1:09:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.15,1:09:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.15,1:09:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.27,1:09:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.27,1:09:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.67,1:10:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.67,1:10:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.80,1:10:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You've had your moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.96,1:10:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.96,1:10:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now keep the peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.96,1:10:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Our teacher used to go like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.96,1:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now button up your...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.96,1:10:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Recess is over.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.98,1:10:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Button up your lips.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.98,1:10:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.68,1:10:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we got far as far as the unfortunate Mr. Dawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.68,1:10:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And scientism and natural skepticism, as I say, I don't believe skepticism should be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.81,1:10:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.81,1:10:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In a normal human being, over 200, it's unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.81,1:10:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, I can see it probably because...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.26,1:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see why they're skeptical because they're out to do you in, and therefore, they presume
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.26,1:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're out to do them in.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.26,1:10:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.26,1:10:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a defense of negativity because their way...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.64,1:10:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.64,1:10:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask what...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.64,1:10:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we have permission to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.64,1:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask on a mulling and mulling.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.68,1:11:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.68,1:11:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask on a mulling and mulling, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.96,1:11:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The percentage of politicians who are continuously, who routinely lie and deceive is over 80%,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.18,1:11:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,85%.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.18,1:11:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of politicians routinely.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.56,1:11:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't specify where.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.47,1:11:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In America, over 80%, 85%.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.03,1:11:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the world, over 95%, 100%, 99%, 98%, 95%.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.81,1:11:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.22,1:11:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains the evening news, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.61,1:12:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your job is to be cleverly deceptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.61,1:12:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the UN is all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.61,1:12:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the UN calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.61,1:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's there to help mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.68,1:12:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They're out to help their friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.68,1:12:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.68,1:12:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we understand natural skepticism then would be like the skeptic is distrustful of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.57,1:12:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,other people because they themselves are not trustable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.57,1:12:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're trustable, you tend to believe everybody and be sort of naive, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.68,1:12:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You believe everything that everybody says is true unless proven otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.71,1:12:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the bottom-up position, which is typical of today's scientism.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.00,1:12:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The vanity of the ego is at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.31,1:13:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so much of our society that you see in the news, Hollywood and all that, it always
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.31,1:13:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.31,1:13:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the vanity of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.31,1:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The vanity of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.35,1:13:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.35,1:13:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So atheism calibrates even lower.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.07,1:13:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.07,1:13:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 165.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.07,1:13:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's making even more of a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.07,1:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's saying that God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.07,1:13:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're honest, you could say you could be an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.50,1:13:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,An agnostic is being more intellectually integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.50,1:13:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectually, you can neither prove nor disprove the reality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.50,1:13:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the purpose of this morning's lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.50,1:13:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There are different paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.56,1:13:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, in the world of logic, you cannot prove the existence of God, but neither
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.56,1:13:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can you disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.56,1:13:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So with humility, so agnosticism is more humble than atheism.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.14,1:14:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Skepticism itself calibrates at 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.14,1:14:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Skepticism then represents the cynicism, in a way, of people who have feelings about the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.42,1:14:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.42,1:14:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They have faith in their own thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.43,1:14:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of their thinking, they say, and of course they ridicule faith, but the skeptic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.03,1:14:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,has profound faith in their own skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.59,1:14:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a dictionary of skepticism, and the person is egoistic all over the place about
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.10,1:14:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,his own capacity to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.10,1:14:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But he thinks on a very pedestrian level.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.10,1:14:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only thinks in the linear domain, the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.10,1:14:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So to the skeptic, the non-linear domain has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.10,1:15:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So anybody who believes in God is obviously a fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.10,1:15:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, paradoxically, anybody who believes in faith is an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.68,1:15:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say that, they make that statement with great faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.68,1:15:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith is an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.68,1:15:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.68,1:15:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.68,1:15:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The other reason skepticism is so low is because it's a variant of nihilism.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.68,1:15:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nihilism is that nothing means anything, nothing is of any value.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.84,1:15:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it negates the value of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.23,1:15:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of aligned with Dawkins' view of the world is the so-called God gene, a famous
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.23,1:15:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,book by Dean Hamer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.23,1:15:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It also calibrates about 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.23,1:15:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is sort of pseudo-science.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.63,1:15:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It disproves God.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.63,1:15:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hypothesis, this arose because of the testimony of so many people with near-death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.63,1:16:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences, or out-of-body experiences, or a combination of the two, that had to be answered.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.56,1:16:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was an attempt to answer, why is it that the near-death experience all over the,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.56,1:16:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the ages, for thousands of years, has been almost identical?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.81,1:16:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.81,1:16:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the religionist sees it as merely, you know, confirmation over and over
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.55,1:16:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,again in different circumstances of an ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.60,1:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The near-death experience is profound, profound, permanent, profound and permanent.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.43,1:16:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So they wanted to know, what can they do about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.43,1:16:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So then they came up with a hypothesis that if you're near death, your brain automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.47,1:16:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,activates a certain node.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.47,1:16:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Activates a certain neuronal circuit and creates this near-death experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.47,1:17:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's a genetic abnormality or weirdness of the neurologic circuits.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.97,1:17:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too bright a theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.97,1:17:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, they never found a God gene, so it calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.44,1:17:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it should calibrate lower, but I'd give it about a 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.11,1:17:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you see the narcissism of scientism.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.81,1:17:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more arrogant and dogmatic than scientism.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.92,1:17:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And debunkers are probably the top of the list.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.10,1:17:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're smug vanity as they try to disprove something by setting up some poppycock experiment
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.10,1:17:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that imitates the real.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.10,1:17:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that they've imitated the real, they've disproven the real, which is a non-sequitur.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.10,1:17:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you can imitate the real.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.10,1:17:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That you can imitate a miracle doesn't prove that a real miracle doesn't occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.84,1:18:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the miracles that I experienced would be beyond duplication anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.39,1:18:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you could duplicate the experiences I've had.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.84,1:18:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And every day there's the unfoldment of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.02,1:18:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll get to science and I've said a few people now pretty soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.06,1:18:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate everybody being so calm out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.06,1:18:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The big bang source of the universe calibrates at 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.27,1:18:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Any big bangers out there upset?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.94,1:18:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to upset any big bangers.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.77,1:18:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But the big banger, like the god gene, the big bang source of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.26,1:18:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the universe arose out of an energy, but it doesn't tell you where the energy arose from.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.26,1:18:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So big bang is without any source of the big bang, and that's why it only calibrates at 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.56,1:18:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming of human origin is false.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.56,1:19:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming of human origin is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.05,1:19:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at, the recent report to the UN about a week ago, the report calibrates at 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.52,1:19:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I first calibrated that some years ago, I thought, well I know the earth is warming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.65,1:19:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But the presumption then, and it's become an ism, an environmental ism.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.97,1:19:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming of human origin, it's not of human origin.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.97,1:19:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The cyclic temperature of the planet is due to the magnetic activity of the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.02,1:19:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It had nothing to do with humankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.02,1:19:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And core drillings in the Arctic, down to 10,000 years ago or 20,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.38,1:19:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,show the concordance of periods, of cyclic periods of warmth.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.97,1:20:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the, if we ask, let's ask, you don't have to get up on your hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.84,1:20:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If the cyclic warming is due to the earth, due to the sun's surface magnetic activity, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.31,1:20:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we find there's any disparity between popular belief systems, including sense and consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.53,1:20:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness research always turns out to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.53,1:20:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've never had it the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.53,1:20:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've never had it the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.67,1:20:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the first time we did it on earth warming, we got no.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.88,1:20:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you know what the cause of earth warming is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.88,1:20:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you the secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.88,1:20:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called overpopulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.88,1:20:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.94,1:20:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.94,1:20:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, there's the pollution.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.94,1:20:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.94,1:20:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, earth warming is not due to pollution.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.94,1:20:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's due to cyclic magnetic activity of the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.97,1:21:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And pollution is a different thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.77,1:21:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the bigger mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.77,1:21:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to mix the two.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.81,1:21:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth, in other words, human pollution is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.81,1:21:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.81,1:21:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not causally related.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.06,1:21:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause of pollution on the earth is overpopulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.06,1:21:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Overpopulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.64,1:21:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A zillion people, and they're multiplying constantly, are sending up all kinds of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.64,1:21:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that causes pollution.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.64,1:21:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But the pollution affects the earth's temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.68,1:21:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,0.8 degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.47,1:21:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth's temperature is affected.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.47,1:21:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,0.8 degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.72,1:21:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so all the fuss is about a very minuscule variation in earth temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.72,1:21:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to cut down the pollution is to have fewer people.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.60,1:21:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's easy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.31,1:22:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop you-know-what.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.27,1:22:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.27,1:22:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought there might be some skeptics here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.27,1:22:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I came prepared for skeptics.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.85,1:22:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Skeptics?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.85,1:22:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Any skeptics?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.85,1:22:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought somebody might poo-poo it because, you know, it's become such a big movement, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.61,1:22:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's become an ism.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.61,1:22:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's become an ism.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.61,1:22:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets politicized in an ism.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.64,1:22:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you the references.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.64,1:22:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be on a videotape anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.64,1:22:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Save people sending me emails.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.68,1:22:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tape your email.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.72,1:22:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The suns serve as magnetic activity, as a source of temperature variation.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.72,1:22:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The reference is J. Lair, L-E-H-R, and F. Bennett, B-E-N-N-E-T-T, article,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.72,1:23:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Sun, in Environment and Climate News, 6-4, May.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.72,1:23:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's another reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.81,1:23:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mailman, uncertainties and projections of human-caused global warming, in the Journal of Science, 278, November.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.81,1:23:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,November, 1997.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.81,1:23:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, those are just scientific references because otherwise I get emails, indignant emails.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.59,1:23:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd just anticipate that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.67,1:23:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because once a thing becomes an ism, it gets religionized.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.35,1:23:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And people are willing to parade and sacrifice and go to battle over it and sue everybody and start a war.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.60,1:23:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth's warming of human origin is not correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.60,1:24:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Parallel universe theory is also incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.18,1:24:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a recent study that got a lot of publicity in the Journal of Cardiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.18,1:24:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So-called negative prayer healing study.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.25,1:24:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrated at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.25,1:24:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradoxically, it was financed by the Templeton Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.40,1:24:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the defect is in the setting up.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.64,1:24:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So many things, what happens is big money becomes available.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.67,1:24:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondhand smoke is another big one.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.67,1:24:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondhand smoke doesn't cause any diseases at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.05,1:24:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that smoking is good for your health, but secondhand smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.05,1:24:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the only way you get a grant, it causes crib death, it causes psoriasis, it causes all these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.27,1:24:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it finally reached such a point that a federal court reviewed all the documentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.30,1:25:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondhand smoke has absolutely no effect health-wise to a measurable degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.30,1:25:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we build these isms that become a religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.30,1:25:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And no-smoking-ism and earth-pollution-ism and earth-warming-ism become very, like Marecke said, delusions and madness of crowds.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.47,1:25:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Negation of faith calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.47,1:25:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Negate non-linear reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.09,1:25:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is context.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.09,1:25:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Puts you at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.09,1:25:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the difficulty of the skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.09,1:25:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic negates the reality, the non-linear realities, which is context.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.22,1:25:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they're left with a pedestrian, sort of lower mind kind of, being literal.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.36,1:25:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In which you have only the linear, but the meaning, the meaning is, they don't understand the meaning because they don't have a context.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.52,1:25:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because context is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.52,1:26:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.60,1:26:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have an interesting comparison.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.60,1:26:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick, you know, discoverer along with Watson of the DNA.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.51,1:26:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The research he did that discovered the secret of the DNA was calibrated about 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.82,1:26:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't he get a Nobel Prize or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.82,1:26:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or he should have?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.82,1:26:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Crick was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.01,1:26:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.01,1:26:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of consciousness is neuronal, was the last research he was doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.39,1:26:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So the prior research on DNA calibrated 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.39,1:26:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of his death, he'd gotten grants for some university to prove that consciousness is a product of neuronal activity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.39,1:26:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, life arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.39,1:26:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Life arises from neuronal activity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.39,1:27:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrated at 140.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.39,1:27:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,140.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.39,1:27:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.39,1:27:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, this was merely a pseudo-science, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.39,1:27:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To prove, sort of like looking for the God gene.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.43,1:27:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the same man at one level.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.43,1:27:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's scientifically integrous at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.43,1:27:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In another, he's trying to prove a proposition.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.43,1:27:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That consciousness is the product of neuronal activity.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.46,1:27:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the bottom-up theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.46,1:27:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom-up theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.46,1:27:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolutionary psychology misses that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.84,1:27:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's also tempted to try and explain everything in Darwinian evolutionary terms.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.57,1:27:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin's theory of evolution calibrated at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.64,1:27:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel Dennett moves into evolutionary psychology.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.02,1:27:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He was on the same issue of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.02,1:27:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He was on the same issue of Time magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.02,1:28:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And Collins was also in the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.02,1:28:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He discovered the genome.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.09,1:28:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.09,1:28:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So they weren't out to try to disprove anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.31,1:28:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Creationism is a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.31,1:28:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at 245.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.31,1:28:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means it's an honest limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.31,1:28:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's insufficient explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.51,1:28:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This stands in contrast.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.51,1:28:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis calibrated at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.64,1:28:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.64,1:28:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the beginning was the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.89,1:28:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we explain the evolution of the human ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.89,1:28:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we always say,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.89,1:28:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead arose the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.96,1:28:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,God as Creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.07,1:28:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.81,1:28:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Means it's not defined yet in terms of creativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.93,1:28:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of the Godhead is the infinite potential of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.93,1:28:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to be anything and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.93,1:29:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.06,1:29:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Including being the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.06,1:29:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So being the Creator then is not just a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.22,1:29:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God is more than just the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.22,1:29:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the very source out of which a Creator arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.22,1:29:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Godhead is, you might say, the source of Godness.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.22,1:29:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So Genesis calibrated at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.47,1:29:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite many of the things in there that would not be scientifically acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.47,1:29:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The gist of it is that out of the Godhead arose divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.47,1:29:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of all existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.47,1:29:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the source of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.47,1:29:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.56,1:29:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Discovery of the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.97,1:29:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.97,1:29:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.97,1:29:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that's way up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.22,1:29:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's aligned with consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.22,1:30:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's aligned with the reality and the confirmable reality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.22,1:30:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and truth of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.22,1:30:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the source out of which spiritual awareness, etc. arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.22,1:30:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would naturally be aligned with the absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.26,1:30:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.93,1:30:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.93,1:30:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As a theory calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.93,1:30:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Francis Collins in that same issue of Time Magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.43,1:30:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he was the head of the genome product, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.43,1:30:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrote a book called The Language of God at 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.43,1:30:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So he tried to bridge the gap between science
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.43,1:30:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.51,1:30:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent design calibrates at 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.51,1:30:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the creationists, the literal creationists,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.51,1:30:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,don't like intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.51,1:30:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me intelligent design gives both sides an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.51,1:30:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If they really want peace, they could accept this
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.51,1:30:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't include the word God in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.72,1:30:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the reason the fundamentalists don't like that
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.72,1:30:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they were afraid with intelligent design
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.72,1:31:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,God could slip in the back door
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.72,1:31:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it says.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.72,1:31:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,God could slip in the back door.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.43,1:31:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,God could slip in the back door.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.43,1:31:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.52,1:31:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.75,1:31:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in Scope's trial, William Jennings Brandt
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.75,1:31:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember against...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.31,1:31:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, William Jennings Brandt calibrated at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.31,1:31:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarence Darrow was at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.31,1:31:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Clarence Darrow was a scientific skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.55,1:31:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A very intelligent man.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.55,1:31:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, William Jennings Brandt was a man of faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.55,1:31:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing was really set up...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.43,1:31:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scope's trial was set up as a publicity stunt
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.47,1:31:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by the founder of ACLU,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.56,1:31:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,himself calibrated about 190,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.56,1:31:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,together with the town where it occurred.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.85,1:32:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the whole thing was not...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.85,1:32:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was contrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.85,1:32:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.85,1:32:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it was somewhat contaminated
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.96,1:32:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was contrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.39,1:32:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However, each one represented...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.39,1:32:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,truthfully represented what they stood for.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.78,1:32:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,William Jennings Brandt at 505
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.78,1:32:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly stood for what 505 means.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.78,1:32:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarence Darrow at 450
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.78,1:32:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was coming from science.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.78,1:32:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Was coming from science.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.07,1:32:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Darrow couldn't make the headway he wanted to,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.07,1:32:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he went to the ad hominem attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.23,1:32:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell to the ad hominem attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.31,1:32:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, ridiculed things
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.31,1:32:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that are really allegorical things in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.31,1:32:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegorical.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.31,1:32:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All the allegorical things,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.56,1:32:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can remove all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.56,1:32:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the meaning and the significance
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.68,1:32:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the calibration of the Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.68,1:32:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,does not change at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.68,1:33:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether Jonah spent three days in the stomach of a whale
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.72,1:33:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is irrelevant to the truth of Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.72,1:33:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as savior and avatar.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.72,1:33:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.72,1:33:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, it's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.97,1:33:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But they represent two different paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.72,1:33:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So Darrow's paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.72,1:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that of science in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.72,1:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we went over,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.72,1:33:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see why he is stuck in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.72,1:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see why William Jennings Brandt at 505
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.72,1:33:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,represents spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.72,1:33:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just never thought
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.97,1:33:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that the issues got resolved
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.97,1:33:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the disparity of paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.97,1:33:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Thomas Aquinas, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.19,1:33:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.28,1:33:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrote a great textbook
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.44,1:33:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in which he tried to integrate
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.44,1:33:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,both faith and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.55,1:33:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And said that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.60,1:33:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,faith without reason
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.60,1:33:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is deficient and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.60,1:34:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the two of them
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.60,1:34:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforced each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.60,1:34:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That your faith becomes greater
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.60,1:34:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when you add to it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.60,1:34:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual comprehension
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.60,1:34:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.31,1:34:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So St. Thomas Aquinas
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.31,1:34:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.76,1:34:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And Aquinas is really a fallout from Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.76,1:34:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I went to Jesuit University
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.76,1:34:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time I was an atheist
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.76,1:34:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I used to hammer
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.76,1:34:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hammer all of these arguments
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.94,1:34:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for the existence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.94,1:34:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.94,1:34:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.94,1:34:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.94,1:34:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is eternal
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.94,1:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has no first cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.94,1:34:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.42,1:34:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was right as an atheist, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.31,1:34:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all I said is that
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.73,1:34:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the arguments for the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.73,1:34:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as I see it now
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.22,1:34:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are within the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.22,1:35:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.22,1:35:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you can neither prove
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.22,1:35:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or disprove God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.22,1:35:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I went from being an atheist
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.22,1:35:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.22,1:35:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can neither prove
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.69,1:35:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,nor disprove
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.69,1:35:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.43,1:35:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.43,1:35:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution is creation
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.43,1:35:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.43,1:35:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the source of creation
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.64,1:35:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.84,1:35:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty you see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.84,1:35:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with the linear domain is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.84,1:35:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,people tend to think
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.31,1:35:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.31,1:35:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think in terms of cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.31,1:35:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see God as
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.31,1:35:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.18,1:35:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.18,1:35:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the spinning the top
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.18,1:35:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then walked away from it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.18,1:35:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.18,1:35:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.56,1:35:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the mid 400's
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.60,1:35:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sees everything
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.60,1:35:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.60,1:36:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.60,1:36:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with the 400's
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.81,1:36:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when it deals with God
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.81,1:36:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is it begins to see God as a cause
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.81,1:36:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than as an ever present source.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.81,1:36:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A cause goes from here
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.17,1:36:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to there in a time scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.17,1:36:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It deals with force.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.75,1:36:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,God as eternal source
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.35,1:36:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,means that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.35,1:36:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution is continuous
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.35,1:36:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and ongoing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.35,1:36:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the nature
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.35,1:36:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.35,1:36:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They become ever more
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.35,1:36:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.35,1:36:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.35,1:36:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.42,1:36:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cause and source
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.42,1:36:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,makes quite a bit of difference
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.42,1:36:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in understanding Genesis
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.42,1:36:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.42,1:36:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or in discussing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.42,1:36:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,science versus religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.60,1:36:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the ever present
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.56,1:36:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ongoing source.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.56,1:36:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which has no beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.69,1:36:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,has no end.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.69,1:36:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no cause
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.50,1:36:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.50,1:37:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No cause for existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.50,1:37:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.63,1:37:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an ever present source.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.63,1:37:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We all get the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.63,1:37:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,between a cause and a source.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.63,1:37:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody get that?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.63,1:37:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Source is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.63,1:37:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,continuancy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.63,1:37:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And a cause comes and goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.63,1:37:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause came and went.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.63,1:37:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause came and went.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.35,1:37:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,God versus science
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.47,1:37:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,issue of Time magazine
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.47,1:37:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in November
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.47,1:37:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 410
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.47,1:37:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite ambiguous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.47,1:37:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It accomplished
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.47,1:37:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what it meant to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.52,1:37:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Sagan,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.52,1:37:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty well known name,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.52,1:37:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.52,1:37:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now 200 is neither here nor there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.52,1:37:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,200 is sort of neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.52,1:37:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.71,1:37:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.27,1:37:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.27,1:37:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.27,1:37:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither good nor bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.38,1:37:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of nice in a way, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.47,1:37:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The planet and the Earth so.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.47,1:37:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,From dust you arise
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.53,1:37:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and to dust you return.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.53,1:38:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 you arise
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.53,1:38:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you're 200 for a while
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.53,1:38:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you go back to 200 again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.53,1:38:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the linear physical domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.52,1:38:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Theology itself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.52,1:38:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as an intellectual discipline
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.52,1:38:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.52,1:38:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty erudite.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.63,1:38:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.63,1:38:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.63,1:38:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the range
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.63,1:38:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.63,1:38:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.63,1:38:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So theology then
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.88,1:38:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is using the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.88,1:38:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and intellectually
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.88,1:38:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehending religion
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.88,1:38:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.88,1:38:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolutionary psychology
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.01,1:38:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we said is at 210
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.01,1:38:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has its popular authors
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.01,1:38:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.01,1:38:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We said before
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.01,1:38:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick's discovery of DNA
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.01,1:38:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,was at 460
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.01,1:38:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one he was working on
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.01,1:38:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick's source of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.01,1:38:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is only neuronal
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.01,1:38:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is 140.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.01,1:38:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the same person
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.01,1:38:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,could be the author of
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.01,1:38:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,something very erudite
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.01,1:38:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.01,1:38:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.01,1:38:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,something quite fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.01,1:39:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.35,1:39:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,plays very big
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.35,1:39:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in our explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.35,1:39:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.35,1:39:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.35,1:39:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.56,1:39:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heisenberg principle then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.77,1:39:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is the explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.77,1:39:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that the skeptics
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.77,1:39:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the materialists
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.77,1:39:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reductionists
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.93,1:39:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.93,1:39:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't see that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.93,1:39:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness intention
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.39,1:39:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the scientist
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.86,1:39:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to already limit
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.86,1:39:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and characterize
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.86,1:39:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of results
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.86,1:39:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to come up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.25,1:39:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A tractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.25,1:39:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.25,1:39:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.25,1:39:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,explains the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.60,1:39:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.60,1:39:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Big Bang source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.60,1:39:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of universe theory
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.60,1:39:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we said was false.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.72,1:39:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Biofield is 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.72,1:39:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The black hole theory
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.72,1:39:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.72,1:39:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephen Hawking
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.72,1:39:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,black hole theory
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.72,1:39:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was last revised
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.72,1:39:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in 2004
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.72,1:39:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 456.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.72,1:40:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Bootstrap scientific theory
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.14,1:40:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know these are advances
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.14,1:40:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.14,1:40:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and chaos theory
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.14,1:40:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all calibrated around 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.14,1:40:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The collective unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.60,1:40:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.27,1:40:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was discovered by Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.30,1:40:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.46,1:40:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is that a legend?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.46,1:40:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that legendary?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.46,1:40:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that just a psychological concept?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.46,1:40:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is the collective unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.68,1:40:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.68,1:40:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We see from a scientific viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.68,1:40:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at 455
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.68,1:40:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.68,1:40:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is somewhat good to know
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.21,1:40:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in some ways
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.21,1:40:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no explaining
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.21,1:40:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how certain people
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.68,1:40:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,develop illnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.68,1:40:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they never even heard of.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.68,1:40:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just also finishing editing
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.68,1:40:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a book on lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.68,1:40:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I once did on health and healing
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.68,1:40:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and people tend to manifest
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.84,1:40:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what they hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.84,1:40:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or what has been suggested to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.84,1:40:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But people will say
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.97,1:41:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember ever believing
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.97,1:41:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in that
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.97,1:41:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I never thought
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.97,1:41:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it would apply to me
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.97,1:41:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so how would I manifest it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.97,1:41:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by holding it in mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.97,1:41:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And where you got it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.97,1:41:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,was the collective unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.97,1:41:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it from the collective
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.97,1:41:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,not from the individual.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.47,1:41:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A great many of the illnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.47,1:41:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are picked up as a child.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.47,1:41:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You just hear it on TV
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.47,1:41:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your mother says it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.47,1:41:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it becomes a reality
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.47,1:41:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.47,1:41:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then later on
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.47,1:41:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with unconscious guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.47,1:41:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you manifest it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.51,1:41:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A negative belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.51,1:41:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,plus unconscious guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.47,1:41:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.47,1:41:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,results in the illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.47,1:41:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to try to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.47,1:41:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and undo all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.47,1:41:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the collective unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.80,1:41:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.80,1:41:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.80,1:41:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it was from young
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.80,1:41:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we got the term
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.80,1:41:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,synergicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.80,1:41:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Synergicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.80,1:41:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Synesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.82,1:41:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Synesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.82,1:42:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.82,1:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.94,1:42:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.03,1:42:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So just as I was saying
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.03,1:42:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was writing a chapter
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.03,1:42:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,on God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.03,1:42:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Time magazine came out
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.03,1:42:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with an issue
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.03,1:42:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.03,1:42:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was in November
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.03,1:42:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was writing that chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.03,1:42:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.52,1:42:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.93,1:42:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.93,1:42:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We did the black hole theory
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.93,1:42:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.18,1:42:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.18,1:42:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of neuronal activity.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.18,1:42:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a bottoms up theory
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.18,1:42:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.18,1:42:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates negative
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.18,1:42:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Crick's research
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.18,1:42:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on that did.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.18,1:42:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.25,1:42:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as a technique
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.25,1:42:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as a science
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.25,1:42:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 605.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.40,1:42:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The science of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.40,1:42:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration is 605.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.11,1:42:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.11,1:42:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you've taken the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.11,1:42:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and made it comprehensible
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.27,1:42:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by definition.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.27,1:42:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.27,1:43:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by using a scale
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.27,1:43:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of one to a thousand
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.27,1:43:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you've made it accessible
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.27,1:43:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.81,1:43:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've taken
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.81,1:43:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.81,1:43:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and by using a tool
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.97,1:43:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.97,1:43:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you've made the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.97,1:43:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehensible to the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.97,1:43:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You've somehow crossed over a bridge
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.35,1:43:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at least in a pragmatic
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.35,1:43:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.73,1:43:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.73,1:43:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,can tell you the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.73,1:43:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.73,1:43:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.73,1:43:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.73,1:43:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.77,1:43:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.77,1:43:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as advanced theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.77,1:43:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics shows
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.80,1:43:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is no dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.80,1:43:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in an infinite universe
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.80,1:43:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no center
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.80,1:43:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no center
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.80,1:43:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to an infinite universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.80,1:43:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere is therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.80,1:43:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,equally the same
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.96,1:43:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as everywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.96,1:43:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's outside of time
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.80,1:43:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,any time is equally now.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.80,1:43:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.23,1:44:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration techniques
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.23,1:44:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that Suze and I do all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.23,1:44:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,works is because
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.23,1:44:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere is right here
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.23,1:44:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and every time is right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.43,1:44:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that comprehensible?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.59,1:44:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is dimensionless
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.60,1:44:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no center
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.60,1:44:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is there?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.60,1:44:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere is
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.60,1:44:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so advanced theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.81,1:44:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,if you meditate on it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.81,1:44:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll end up
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.81,1:44:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.81,1:44:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,every place is here
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.81,1:44:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and everywhere is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.81,1:44:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.39,1:44:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.39,1:44:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is accessible to us
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.39,1:44:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,right this instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.39,1:44:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And it happened
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.77,1:44:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side of the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.77,1:44:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's accessible to us
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.77,1:44:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.77,1:44:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The details of ancient Egypt
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.06,1:44:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are as knowable right now
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.06,1:44:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as they were at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.15,1:44:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the first world war.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.15,1:44:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They're occurrences.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.44,1:44:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What the various people thought
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.44,1:44:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what they did, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.44,1:44:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a little hard for people
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.57,1:44:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck in the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.57,1:45:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the skeptic especially
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.57,1:45:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand how consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.57,1:45:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration could transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.57,1:45:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,time and distance and space
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.84,1:45:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.84,1:45:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and come out with an answer
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.96,1:45:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which in their paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.96,1:45:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be knowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.96,1:45:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not knowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.40,1:45:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.40,1:45:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how quickly it's knowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.40,1:45:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How soon can you tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.40,1:45:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.40,1:45:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In an instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.07,1:45:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute the UN report
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.81,1:45:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,came out on global warming
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.81,1:45:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on the news
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.81,1:45:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we instantly did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.23,1:45:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We had it right now and then.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.23,1:45:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.23,1:45:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't have to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.23,1:45:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have to buy any equipment.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.23,1:45:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have to invest any money.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.23,1:45:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Instant now and free.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.06,1:45:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.22,1:45:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.22,1:45:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,like the guy that discovered penicillin
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.22,1:45:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the same reason to be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.22,1:45:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He said,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.22,1:45:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, look what you can do with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.22,1:45:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.22,1:45:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.22,1:45:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can know anything about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.22,1:46:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now it didn't cost a second
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.22,1:46:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.22,1:46:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to share it with the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.22,1:46:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.80,1:46:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Distant healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.80,1:46:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a research on that
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.31,1:46:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that turned out to be negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.36,1:46:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity as source of the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.39,1:46:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinitely true.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.39,1:46:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Drake equation
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.85,1:46:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.85,1:46:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the probability of life
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.85,1:46:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,being on other planets
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.85,1:46:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in this galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.39,1:46:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The probability of the Drake equation
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.39,1:46:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is about 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.39,1:46:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's some other things
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.90,1:46:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're not going to lay awake about
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.90,1:46:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but you might worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.90,1:46:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth's magnetic field is weakening.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.90,1:46:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.90,1:46:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They are.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.31,1:46:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you got something to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.18,1:46:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth's magnetic fields are weakening.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.18,1:46:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.18,1:46:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.18,1:46:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Earth is slowly reversing
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.18,1:47:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,its magnetic poles.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.18,1:47:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.56,1:47:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do with your compass?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.14,1:47:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth is moving gradually
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.55,1:47:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,towards the south.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.55,1:47:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's some interesting maps of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.55,1:47:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It wavers.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.55,1:47:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The magnetic pole is wavering.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.55,1:47:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the poles
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.55,1:47:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are slowly reversing.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.55,1:47:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming due to pollution
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.00,1:47:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we've asked this in a number of different
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.00,1:47:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,language styles.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.00,1:47:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It still comes out.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.00,1:47:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnetic surface cycling,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.00,1:47:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.00,1:47:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,E equals mc squared.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.76,1:47:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have I heard that?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.76,1:47:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.47,1:47:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the power
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.47,1:47:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of scientific proof at 455
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.47,1:47:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,equals mc squared.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.47,1:47:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.63,1:47:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who was in the Arizona
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.63,1:47:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Republic about a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.63,1:47:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He keeps writing books denouncing
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.63,1:47:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein's theory as hokum.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.63,1:47:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He does.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.63,1:48:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's on his fourth book or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.63,1:48:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been at it for decades.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.63,1:48:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He writes all the
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.88,1:48:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,scientists around.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.07,1:48:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The emperor who wears
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.07,1:48:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,no clothes or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.07,1:48:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he calls Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.07,1:48:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.07,1:48:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He writes all these books.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.07,1:48:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a big article in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.07,1:48:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's up to his fourth book or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.19,1:48:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.19,1:48:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just thought
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.28,1:48:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd like to know that
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.28,1:48:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,E equals mc squared
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.28,1:48:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,passes the muster.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.80,1:48:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic who doubts
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.93,1:48:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.93,1:48:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How does he explain
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.93,1:48:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima and Nagasaki?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.93,1:48:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.93,1:48:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If Einstein's theory wasn't correct
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.93,1:48:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,how'd he explain the atomic bomb?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.93,1:48:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed to me
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.93,1:48:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that would put it into
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.93,1:48:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.93,1:48:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But skepticism, although it claims
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.93,1:48:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,reason, is really immune to reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.38,1:48:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,E equals mc squared.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.38,1:49:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.38,1:49:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery of the last century.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.38,1:49:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein named the man of the century.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.38,1:49:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.76,1:49:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The god gene we said was negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.76,1:49:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Greenhouse gas earth warming theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.76,1:49:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, it comes up no matter how we phrase it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.76,1:49:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart math on the other hand
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.76,1:49:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which has to do with frequencies
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.76,1:49:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.76,1:49:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg uncertainty
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.76,1:49:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,principle itself is at 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.76,1:49:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Homesis is a
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.76,1:49:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific theory that a little of
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.76,1:49:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,something will immunize you against a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.76,1:49:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.76,1:49:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That this is a holographic
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.11,1:49:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,universe is 395.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.11,1:49:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really a scientific
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.11,1:49:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.11,1:49:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What it's saying is that this has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.11,1:49:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.11,1:49:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but how you're conceptualizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.11,1:49:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The inflation
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.65,1:49:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,theory of the origin of the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.65,1:49:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the post big bang theory
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.65,1:49:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the world
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.65,1:49:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is expanding at the rate of
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.65,1:49:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.65,1:50:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.65,1:50:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.85,1:50:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be done with this
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.43,1:50:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,science by lunch, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.43,1:50:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have five minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.88,1:50:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Five minutes left?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.88,1:50:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Page one, page two.
